Orchestrates Passes A (count expansion) and B (type append) plus line-flag resolution, transforming parsed AST entries into `TypedEntry` records for rendering.

`expand_dict(entries, generic_arg_strokes)` is the entry point: it builds the type set from `@type` declarations (which are consumed, not emitted), optionally filters arity-0 types by `generic_arg_strokes`, then threads each non-type entry through `expand_counts` (resolving repeat/dcount/computed) and `expand_types_one` (resolving type slots), calls `fix_family_terminals` to mark non-terminal steps, and finishes with `expand_line_flag` to set the U one-liner flag.

`ExpandedEntry` (Pass A output) holds count-resolved chunks with the source `Entry`. `TypedEntry` (Pass B output) adds `terminal` and `one_liner` flags plus the resolved `type_label` from the `%t` slot. Both carry the original `Entry` for provenance. The stroke field includes any appended type strokes only on `TypedEntry`.

The submodules implement the passes and type machinery; the re-exports expose entry points (`expand_counts`, `expand_types_one`, `expand_line_flag`) and utilities consumed by renderers elsewhere in the crate.